  "claim_short": "2410.10678 algebraic numerical range Example 6.3 asks whether the constant 2 sqrt(3) / 3 in inequality (6.1) is optimal. The classical Bohr-Bombieri majorant formula gives B(1/2)=6-2 sqrt(6), hence the estimate for T=E direct sum (1/2)L improves from 2 sqrt(3)/3 to 6-2 sqrt(6). This is a literature-implied answer to the optimality part only; the constant-1 polynomially bounded operator with Psi(T)=infinity remains...",
